title: Liverpool earns uninspiring Europa draw ahead of Merseyside derby
text:
Liverpool earns uninspiring Europa draw ahead of Merseyside derby FOXSports 1 hr ago © Getty Images LIVERPOOL, ENGLAND - OCTOBER 01: Adam Lallana of Liverpool (L) celebrates scoring the opening goal wth Danny Ings of Liverpool during the UEFA Europa League group B match between Liverpool FC and FC Sion at Anfield on October 1, 2015 in Liverpool, United Kingdom. (Photo by Dean Mouhtaropoulos/Getty Images) Liverpool remain without a win in the Europa League after FC Sion recovered from Adam Lallana’s early goal to claim a 1-1 draw at Anfield.
Looking to build on Saturday’s 3-2 win over Aston Villa, Liverpool got off to the best possible start when Lallana steered home following good work from Divock Origi, one of seven changes made by Brendan Rodgers, in just the fourth minute.
AdChoices However, Ebenezer Assifuah stabbed home an equaliser 13 minutes later, and FC Sion managed to withstand plenty of late pressure from the hosts to claim a point.
